\begin_layout Standard
In a fixed income security, the formula is fixed upfront.
 It might be very simple, or complicated (depend on the BOI interest rate).
 Its important feature is that it is 
\series bold
not subject to performance
\series default
.
 It has the first priority in the cash flows (before the equity holders)
 and lower risk.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The amounts or the dates are not fixed, only the formula is.
\end_layout

